description:
In lichen_lora_l2_stop(), the join logic waits up to RX_THREAD_QUICK_JOIN_MS + RX_TIMEOUT_MS before aborting:

```c
int join_ret = k_thread_join(&rx_thread_data, K_MSEC(RX_THREAD_QUICK_JOIN_MS));
if (join_ret == -EAGAIN) {
    join_ret = k_thread_join(&rx_thread_data, K_MSEC(RX_TIMEOUT_MS));
    if (join_ret == -EAGAIN) {
        LOG_WRN("RX thread join timed out after %dms...",
                RX_THREAD_QUICK_JOIN_MS + RX_TIMEOUT_MS);
        k_thread_abort(&rx_thread_data);
        k_thread_join(&rx_thread_data, K_FOREVER);
        ...
    }
}
```

With defaults: RX_THREAD_QUICK_JOIN_MS (100) + RX_TIMEOUT_MS (typically 1000-5000ms) = 1.1 to 5.1 seconds total worst case.

This is documented in the header's docstring ('Blocks until RX thread exits'), but the actual maximum block time is:
- Best case: instant (thread already exited)
- Typical case: <100ms (exits between lora_recv calls)
- Worst case: RX_THREAD_QUICK_JOIN_MS + RX_TIMEOUT_MS + abort time

Impact: P3 - documentation/expectations issue. The behavior is correct for the semantics, but callers may not expect multi-second blocks on stop().
